  "prompt": "I told him I liked him and he didn't give me an actual answer! Help?",
  "response": "I'm really sorry you're feeling this way. It can be incredibly frustrating and painful when you open up about your feelings and don't receive a clear response. Here are a few steps you might consider to navigate this situation:\n\n1. **Give It Some Time**: Sometimes, people need time to process their emotions and thoughts. He might be unsure about his feelings or how to respond, especially if the conversation was unexpected for him.\n\n2. **Seek Clarity**: If some time has passed and you're still feeling uncertain, consider reaching out to him for a more direct conversation. You might say something like, \"I wanted to follow up on what I shared earlier. I'm looking to understand how you feel about it.\"\n\n3. **Reflect on Your Feelings and Needs**: Take some time to think about what you want moving forward. Are you hoping for a relationship, or do you value the friendship as it is? Understanding your own feelings can help guide your next steps.\n\n4. **Maintain Open Communication**: Clear and honest communication is key in any relationship. Expressing your feelings openly can encourage him to do the same, leading to a better understanding between both of you.\n\n5. **Seek Support**: Talking to trusted friends or a counselor can provide you with emotional support and different perspectives on the situation. They can help you process your feelings and decide on the best course of action.\n\n6. **Take Care of Yourself**: Regardless of the outcome, prioritize your well-being. Engage in activities that make you happy and surround yourself with supportive people.\n\nRemember, it's important to respect both your feelings and his. While it's natural to seek clarity, it's also okay to give each other space to understand and navigate emotions. Whatever happens, take care of yourself and know that your feelings are valid.",
